description: Agoric provides a framework for programming smart contracts securely and with ease, beyond anything available today.

full_description:
Agoric is a framework that provides security and ease in programming smart contracts, beyond anything available today. Agoric’s mission is to provide a secure smart contracts framework to the entire blockchain ecosystem. With Agoric, which makes it easier to build and deploy smart contracts in JavaScript, millions of programmers worldwide will have safer, simpler tools to build smart contracts and applications. In addition, composability enables rapid development and competitive advantage. With secure smart contracts, we envision unprecedented, widespread forms of global cooperation, and entrepreneurs creating fundamentally new businesses enabled by digital assets. Agoric is here to make that opportunity a reality.

The Agoric team includes world-class technologists, economists, business leaders and community builders on a quest to bring smart contracts into the future. Members of the Agoric team have been professional collaborators in smart contracts technology for over 30 years, and have now reunited to enact this mission. Agoric has collaborated with Cosmos and other well-known projects, and is backed by Outlier Ventures, Kilowatt Capital, gumi Cryptos Capital, MetaStable Capital, Lemniscap, Xpring, Rockaway Blockchain and the Interchain Foundation, as well as additional funding from Naval Ravikant and Polychain.

full_description:

description: Auxon is a software company that enables AI & systems engineers to build safe, resilient systems.

industry_groups: Artificial Intelligence, Data and Analytics, Hardware, Information Technology, Science and Engineering, Software
full_description:
Auxon is a software company that enables AI & systems engineers to build safe, resilient systems. It is a highly-automated system that requires tight integration of complex hardware & software that must interact predictably and safely with the physical world. This increasing complexity has led to expensive production delays, safety recalls, and cyber-security breaches as emergent failures become increasingly commonplace. 

Auxon’s advanced software tools provide users with continuous, intelligent analysis of potential system problems during development and after deployment, so they can get to market faster with safer, more resilient, and more secure products. The company's continuous verification & validation platform proactively expose hidden system flaws to help you avoid systematic failures while engineering for resilience against random faults.

description: It's an all-in-one platform
industries: CRM, Home Services, Marketplace, Mobile Apps, Real Estate, SaaS, Service Industry, Software
industry_groups: Apps, Commerce and Shopping, Information Technology, Mobile, Other, Real Estate, Sales and Marketing, Software
full_description:
ChoreRelief provides a transparent, competitive marketplace for consumers to manage home repairs. The app connects consumers with contractors and home improvement professionals in order to create a worry-free experience.

ChoreRelief combines the main elements of both networks and marketplaces. We use SaaS workflow software to focus action around longer-term projects, not just a quick transaction. The tool lets repair and maintenance professionals perform critical tasks, send bids, and collect payments, etc. It promotes these service providers as differentiated individuals, helping build long-term relationships with clients.

It also permits property managers, landlords, and homeowners with an opportunity to post their repair and maintenance needs, and optionally, the budget within which they’re working. This streamlines the match-making process for both parties.

Customers and providers are each unique; they are not interchangeable commodities as with Lyft or Uber. Each person brings unique expertise, needs, and viewpoints to the transaction and the relationship. Our market network is designed to acknowledge that as a core tenet and provide solutions that accommodate it. The company’s mission is to expand globally while seamlessly connecting property owners with contractors. The result is more accessible talent, affordable rates, a single source for the endless needs of property owners, and more business for contractors.

We view ourselves as innovators and collaborators, not competitors. That’s why we do our best to build networks that promote collaboration among contractors. It’s the underlying focus of everything we do because we want to solve problems for everyone using technology who wants to join us and make history.

description: Corsha’s API Security Platform prevents network attacks through dynamic, fully automated multi-factor authentication for APIs.
industries: Cloud Security, Cyber Security, IT Infrastructure, SaaS, Security
industry_groups: Information Technology, Privacy and Security, Software
full_description:
Corsha is a leading cybersecurity company that is defining the landscape of API security.  APIs are the glue that stitch together hybrid and multi-cloud networks. Our game-changing API Security Platform solves the growing security concerns facing enterprises as attacks on APIs increase.  Our platform empowers CTOs, CISOs and other security professionals to protect their data and applications as they traverse hybrid and multi-cloud environments.

Corsha has developed the first and only dynamic, fully automated multi-factor authentication (MFA) for APIs.  We protect APIs using the same MFA principles that have successfully protected systems from human username/password cyberattacks.

By enabling MFA for every API call, our platform cryptographically defines the network so that only authorized machines can connect to applications and data, resulting in a dynamic identity for every deployed machine.  

Through our central management console, security professionals have full visibility into and complete control of all API activity across cloud and enterprise networks.

Our platform is deployed as Corsha Cloud (SaaS) or Corsha Enterprise (self-hosted).  It integrates with modern DevOps pipelines and is cloud-native, highly scalable, and platform agnostic.

description: DIRT is a protocol for decentralized information curation that uses token staking to incentivize honesty.
industry_groups: Information Technology
full_description:
DIRT is a protocol for decentralized information curation that uses token staking to incentivize honesty. DIRT is not a Token Curated Registry (TCR). DIRT is a protocol to build TCRs. 

Similar to Wikipedia, DIRT allows anyone to contribute information. DIRT maintains accuracy at scale because every contributor needs to deposit tokens to write data. If the data is correct, it is freely shared. If the data is incorrect, anyone can challenge the data and earn tokens for identifying these inaccurate facts. Their protocol and platform makes it economically irrational for misinformation to persist in a data set.

description: PlayNice is the first platform to legally stop cyberbullying.
headquarters: New York, New York, United States
industry_groups: Apps, Internet Services, Mobile, Platforms, Software
full_description:
PlayNice is the first App to legally stop CyberBullying. Using the same
Confidentiality Agreements that celebrities use, PlayNice allows anyone to access
the tools to keep themselves and people they know, protected from online abuse
and CyberBullying. Send and sign these agreements with people you meet online or
already know, and agree to one limitation on the relationship; never harm each other
online. If the agreement is broken, PlayNice has a suite of tools to enforce the
agreement, help remove the harmful content, and hold the offender accountable.

For years, the celebrities have used confidentiality agreements and NDA’s to keep
their private lives, private. They have been proven to work but the legal fees can cost
a fortune, and generally, they exist in a clunky paper format and are not easy to sign
and maintain. PlayNice makes it easy and accessible for all by allowing people on
the App to easily sign and protect each other, and store the agreements safely on the
App. PlayNice’s goal is for the millennial market to be the first generation to take
control of their online privacy and digital footprint, and not allow people they know
to forever damage their reputation online.

description: PharmID provides accurate verification of the medication and concentration in pharmaceutical products within seconds.
industries: Health Care, Hospital, Information Technology, Medical Device
industry_groups: Health Care, Information Technology
full_description:
PharmID provides accurate verification of the medication and concentration in pharmaceutical products within seconds. It utilizes MarqMetrix patented chemical verification technology to precisely and accurately identify the chemical make-up of medications in the hospital and the non-acute care marketplace. 

MarqMetrix has been providing non-destructive quantitative and qualitative Raman Spectroscopy tools and services to industrial clients (petro- and agri-chemical, pharmaceutical, and others) for the last 5+ years. Two of the founders of PharmID have family connections in pharmacy, so it was only a matter of time before the connection of Raman Spectroscopy to assist pharmacy in identification and verification of medications was made.

PharmID is currently pursuing products to support drug diversion prevention, IV compounding verification, and other activities where knowing for certain what-the-drug-is important.

PharmID was founded in early 2017 to develop and commercialize technology developed by MarqMetrix for healthcare and pharmacy uses.

description: InOrbit is a cloud-based robot management platform to help robotics developers and operators scale their robot fleets.
industries: Artificial Intelligence, Cloud Data Services, Enterprise Software, Robotics, SaaS
industry_groups: Artificial Intelligence, Data and Analytics, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Science and Engineering, Software
full_description:
InOrbit is bridging the autonomy gap through a cloud robot management platform that enables robotics companies and operators to develop, deploy and orchestrate autonomous robots at global scale. The commercial service robot market, is growing over 40% YoY and is expected to hit $50B by 2024.

InOrbit is pioneering the new field of RobOps, or DevOps for Robotics -- think of it as Splunk/Datadog for Robots. InOrbit’s multi-cloud platform provides secure, real-time analytics and data collection, robot performance monitoring (RPM), incident management and remote interventions. The company’s proprietary technology, including adaptive diagnostics and predictive analytics, is able to derive unique value by leveraging industry-wide data that provides InOrbit’s customer’s insight they are unable to obtain on their own.  InOrbit has access to over 300 Petabytes of data per month and can learn faster than any robotics company by operating across different robots and industry verticals. Customers and partners include Google, Qualcomm, Sprint, Brain Corp., Bossa Nova Robotics and over a dozen other robot manufacturers that range from early stage to scaling. 

InOrbit’s founding team includes Mario Munich, a pioneer in robotics and former SVP Technology at iRobot (through acquisition of Evolution Robotics, where he was CTO); Julian Cerruti, an expert in complex systems, robotics and augmented reality (experience with Willow Garage, creator of de facto standard Robot Operating System, Savioke, Clearpath, Google, IBM); and Florian Pestoni, with experience leading product teams reaching hundreds of millions of users at large-scale cloud companies (formerly at Microsoft, Adobe, Atlassian, Facebook, Ooyala). Together the team holds well over 50 patents in security, autonomous navigation, image processing, distributed systems and collaboration, with diverse experience including starting companies, scaling teams, shipping products at scale and achieving venture-backed exit through acquisition.

description: Easy to use property management software for small-to-mid-sized landlords.

full_description:

Landlords can collect rent via ACH or credit cards. Users can set rents, configure late fees, waive fees if needed and manage recurring charges like parking fees and utility bills. Email reminders are sent to tenants before rent is due, when rent is due and if a payment is late. Innago also includes invoice generation, late fee assessment, account deposits and invoice tracking. Multiple bank accounts are supported.

Esignature tools let tenants sign leases remotely from mobile or desktop devices. Landlords and tenants can access documents remotely as well, built-in lease templates allow users to configure rental amounts, lease dates and pet addendums. Users can also add, remove, and sublease tenants. Communication tools let users contact individuals or entire properties.

Our mission is to make renting simple, accessible, and affordable for landlords of any size. Innago is 100% free to use and comes with a long list of affordable features.

First, they’re building it into Messenger. This means you don’t have to visit a dedicated site each day and navigate a complicated UI – you just open Messenger and start chatting with their bot, which walks you through entering games and creating lineups.

It’s also totally free to play, which also cuts down on the intimidation factor and makes it fan (and family) friendly. Users can select real prizes like apparel and gift cards that can be bought with in-app currency awarded to contest winners.

   HomeSirens is also unique in the way that any company can run their own version of HomeSirens and control the cloud security updates and logic according to their company defined policies. description: Building connections one conversation at a time.
industries: Consumer, Dating, Lifestyle, Mobile Apps, Social Network
industry_groups: Apps, Community and Lifestyle, Internet Services, Mobile, Other, Software
full_description:
The COVID-19 pandemic brought the world to a halt. Singles found themselves feeling more alone now than ever. Couples, who once stood strong during their greatest challenges, are now crumbling under the weight of the stresses the pandemic has brought. The pandemic forced us all to change how we live our lives and to think about what’s most important: the need and desire for a deeper connection with someone. 

Singles need help connecting during actual dates (because this is where dating apps fail) and couples need help starting conversations beyond work, finances, schedules and kids. So how do you form a connection and maintain it?

For singles looking to form a genuine connection on actual dates and couples looking to maintain their connection, 3rdDegree is the ice-breaking game that facilitates new levels of open communication. It’s a connection building app that takes honesty and vulnerability to create high quality conversations. It encourages face to face communication to build a connection by two people getting to ask the date questions we all want to know. Through game-like quizzes that score you based on your effort to open up, you will find out new, fun tidbits about your person. With questions that foster a deeper connection to help reveal the true essence of a person, singles can see if they truly are a good match beyond surface level and couples are motivated by the delight in unexpected discoveries of one another. 

Dig deeper with 3rdDegree on first dates, following dates, or throughout a lifetime together.

full_description:
Markaaz created a platform to verify and connect every small business on the planet and the network of partners that support them. By listening to small business owners and understanding the challenges they face, we’ve reimagined what is possible with best-in-class technology, strategic partners, and a world-class team of executives and advisors, all dedicated to creating positive and sustainable impact for SMBs. The company's partners like Salesforce and Equifax join us on the mission to provide small business owners with accessible and affordable resources and tools to run, manage and grow their businesses.

The Markaaz Directory is an unrivaled resource of more than 100 million pre-vetted SMBs that allows business owners to save critical time and money to identify, connect and transact with already verified suppliers and partners. It is the first to offer SMBs affordable access to the highest standards for compliance and risk assessment checks for suppliers and partners.

During 2021, Markaaz expands the platform with an all-in-one Dashboard where small businesses can find integrated solutions (from CRM to accounting, supply chain, cybersecurity, and everything in between) and access toolkits that solve business- or industry-specific challenges – all designed to help them thrive. 

Powered by a natural language AI chatbot, the Markaaz Directory and Dashboard connect and empower businesses like never before.

full_description: Terraseed Multivitamin resolves the nine most common gaps in a plant-based diet while ensuring ethical and sustainable practices that align with the vegan ideals of protecting the environment and animal lives.  Terraseed replaces animal-based ingredients for vegan options. For example, its Omega-3 is sourced from algae harvested without impact on marine ecosystems, and D3 is sourced from wild lichen instead of sheep’s wool.  It is also into sustainable packaging, particularly forgoing the traditional plastic pill bottle in favor of a compostable alternative.  From the first-ever mailers printed with algae ink, to tamper-resistant cellulose made from corn, every element of the bottle and packaging has been thoughtfully selected.
